Add a guestbook to your site easily.

&lt;b&gt;Features:&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It is possible to reply to comments, keeping the order.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Includes pagination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possibility to choose the order in which comments are shown.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;From admin &gt; plugins&gt;guestbook, it is possible to delete comments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The comments are save in /data/othert/logs/guestbook.log.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The backups are saved in in /data/other/logs/guestbook_bak/.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If there is not any comment, in admin&gt;plugins&gt;guestbook, appears a message: *missing guestbook.log*. When some comment is written this log will be created, and saved the comment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In comments, you can put emoticons. The emoticons are in /plugins/guestbook/img\\_emots .  If you want add more emoticons, only you have to paste \*.gif in this folder. If you want delete some emoticons, only you have to delete it from folder.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CSS  system. CSS file is in /plugins/guestbook/guestbook.css.
     There are 4 colors defined; they are to first of file. You can choose the one you like best; simply comment and discomment colour section.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports bbcode.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

