I have created a new plugin that allows a website visitor to increase/decrease the font size of the page content. By default the font size range is 8px to 72px and the tags that can be resized are stored in the font_resizer.js file.

**FIX TO VERSION 1.0 **
In the font_resize.php file change

**FROM**
register_script(&#039;**font_resize**&#039;&#039;,$site_url.&#039;plugins/font_resize/js/font_resize.js&#039;, &#039;0.1&#039;, TRUE);
queue_script(&#039;**font_resize**&#039;,GSFRONT);

**TO**
register_script(&#039;**font_resizer**&#039;,$site_url.&#039;plugins/font_resize/js/font_resize.js&#039;, &#039;0.1&#039;, TRUE);
    queue_script(&#039;**font_resizer**&#039;,GSFRONT);

Version 1.01 has been uploaded with the fix applied.

Sorry for any inconvenience.

Dave

I have created a plugin that allows the admin to reorder the plugins so that content is loaded in the order you want.

 I also added the ability to create a new plugin.xml file so that if a plugin is removed, it will not break the system. The only caveat is that all plugins are enabled by default.

**FIX TO CORRECT ADMIN ISSUES**

**FROM**

register_script(&#039;jquery&#039;, &#039;http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.7.1/jquery.min.js&#039;, &#039;1.7.1&#039;, **TRUE**);
    
queue_script(&#039;jquery&#039;,GSBACK);

register_script(&#039;jqueryui&#039;, &#039;http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jqueryui/1.8.18/jquery-ui.min.js&#039;, &#039;1.8.18&#039;, **TRUE**);

queue_script(&#039;jqueryui&#039;,GSBACK);

**TO**

register_script(&#039;jquery&#039;, &#039;http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.7.1/jquery.min.js&#039;, &#039;1.7.1&#039;, **FALSE**);
    
queue_script(&#039;jquery&#039;,GSBACK);

    register_script(&#039;jqueryui&#039;, &#039;http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jqueryui/1.8.18/jquery-ui.min.js&#039;, &#039;1.8.18&#039;, **FALSE**);
    
queue_script(&#039;jqueryui&#039;,GSBACK);

&lt;div style=&quot;font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 15px;&quot;&gt;

&lt;h3 style=&quot;margin-bottom: 1px;&quot;&gt;FEATURES:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Works with both GS 3.0 and 3.1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Allows including user comments in pages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; List of pages like a blog or news system, with 2 types of layout styles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Settings/options in Admin &gt; Pages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Backup system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; CSS support. CSS file is located in /plugins/pages_comments/pc.css.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Supports both fancy URLs on and off.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Supports bbcode in comments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Link back to list of pages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Sends notification emails using standard function or class phpmailer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Along with then Frontend User plugin, it is possible have user registered comments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Social share: Addthis system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

   &lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt; There are 3 main things we can do with this plugin:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1. ADDING COMMENTS TO GETSIMPLE PAGES CREATED BY GETSIMPLE (in Admin &gt; Pages).&lt;br /&gt;
               To add the comments system to a page simply go to Admin &gt; Pages &gt; Pages&amp;comments:&lt;br /&gt;
         *Button &lt;b&gt;&#039;Add Comments to Pages&#039;&lt;/b&gt;: here you see all pages that don&#039;t have the comments system included. Click on &#039;Add&#039;, and then edit the options to choose if you want captcha, emoticons, etc.&lt;br /&gt;
         It is possible disable comments in a page by selecting the &#039;No&#039; option for the comments; thus this page could be shown in a blog in a list of pages (with the function described in point 2).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br /&gt;

&lt;li&gt;2. CREATING A BLOG / NEWS LIST OF PAGES, you can display them with 2 diferents types of styles: blog style, or list of pages style; you can see the example in : &lt;a href=&quot;http://cumbe.no-ip.biz/gs31/blog-1/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://cumbe.no-ip.biz/gs31/blog-1/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
        This is configurable in &#039;Group options&#039;.&lt;br /&gt;
        It can be organized by groups, and you can put them in categories, that later can be used to show all the pages  of the same category.&lt;br /&gt;
        To create a blog or a list of pages, you can just add the function &lt;b&gt;&lt; ?php ls_pagesblg(&#039;yourgroup&#039;); ?&gt;&lt;/b&gt; to your template; or you can insert it in the content of the page (if you use the exec-php or the DynPages plugin).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3. SUPPORT FOR FRONT END USER PLUGIN by mikeh: we can have comments in pages but only let registered or logged in users write comments in that page; example in:  &lt;a href=&quot;http://cumbe.no-ip.biz/gs31/blog/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://cumbe.no-ip.biz/gs31/blog/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
       If a page has ticked on &lt;i&gt;&#039;Members only&#039;&lt;/i&gt; in its configuration in Admin &gt; Edit page, the page will only be visible if the user is logged in.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

